title: tsunemori_akane
body: [b]Tsunemori Akane (常守 朱)[/b] is the main female character of [[Psycho-Pass]]. A young and idealist girl and a brilliant student, Tsunemori opted to join the Public Safety Bureau because she believed that she could make a difference. While very inexperienced and not used to the criminal world, she is shown to have a very strong mind, being able to shrug off the trauma of terrible events relatively easily. She has a strong sense of justice which sometimes doesn't agree with Sybil's decisions, and is generally very courageous. She is also very polite and is easily embarrassed. After the events of the first episode she and Kougami form a bond and she deeply cares for him. Tsunemori is also a pacifist, and has not fired a lethal shot at anyone. In episode 11 [spoiler]Makishima killed her friend Yuki, after which she became determined to catch him. In episode 16 she saves Kougami from being killed by Makishima and narrowly stops herself from killing him in revenge for Yuki.[/spoiler]

title: tachibana_wataru
body:
A supporting character from [[Hayate no Gotoku!]]

Thirteen-year-old fiance of [[Sanzen'in Nagi]], despite neither having feelings for each other - instead, Wataru has a crush on Nagi's best friend [[Saginomiya Isumi]]. He lives in and runs a video-rental store - the last remnant of his family's once vast business enterprise - with his maid [[Kijima Saki]].

title: segawa_izumi
body:
A supporting character from [[Hayate no Gotoku!]]

Class Representative for [[Ayasaki Hayate]]'s class and part of a trio of proud school underachievers, together with classmates [[Asakaze Risa]] and [[Hanabishi Miki]], who hang around with [[Katsura Yukiji]]. Izumi is the daughter of the president of a large manufacturing company, and is frequently the butt of pranks from Risa and Miki. She's also the girl closest to Hayate among the trio.

title: nishizawa_ayumu

She is also good friends with [[Katsura Hinagiku]], who also has a crush on Hayate. The anime adaptation frequently made fun of her rather large appetite.

title: klaus_seishirou
body:
A supporting character from [[Hayate no Gotoku!]]

The 58-year-old head butler of the Sanzen'in household and former personal butler to [[sanzen'in_nagi|Nagi]]'s deceased mother, Yukariko. A self-centered man with low tolerance on alcohol and tobacco, as well as poor communication skills with females.

title: kijima_saki
body:
A supporting character from [[Hayate no Gotoku!]]

Twenty-year-old maid of [[Tachibana Wataru]], who helps him run a video-rental store - the last of the Tachibanas' once prosperous business enterprise. She is very protective of Wataru, even fearing he will start watching porn upon reaching puberty, but greatly fears being touched anywhere by other males, such as [[Ayasaki Hayate]].

title: katsura_yukiji
body:
A supporting character from [[Hayate no Gotoku!]]

[[katsura_hinagiku|Hinagiku]]'s 28-year-old elder sister and history teacher (and also gate guard) at Hakuou Academy. Compared to her orderly younger sister, Yukiji is rather childish, irresponsible and also an alcoholic. She frequently hangs around with a trio of underachieving students - [[Asakaze Risa]], [[Segawa Izumi]] and [[Hanabishi Miki]].

title: katsura_hinagiku
body:
A supporting character from [[Hayate no Gotoku!]]

Student Council President of Hakuou Academy, where [[Ayasaki Hayate]], [[Sanzen'in Nagi]] and [[Saginomiya Isumi]] attend, as well as younger sister of [[katsura_yukiji|Yukiji]], one of the school's teachers. Intelligent, well-mannered (in contrast to her alcoholic older sister) and popular with the girls, Hina, as she is known, is also skilled at kendo. After being saved by Hayate from being stuck on a tree (due to her agoraphobia), she has developed feelings for him.

title: hanabishi_miki
body:
A supporting character from [[Hayate no Gotoku!]]

A member of Hakuou Academy's Student Council, Class Vice-Representative to [[Ayasaki Hayate]]'s class, and part of a trio of proud school underachievers together with [[Asakaze Risa]] and [[Segawa Izumi]], who hang around with [[Katsura Yukiji]]. As the daughter of a government official and granddaughter of a former Prime Minister, Miki is rather inquisitive, and enjoys causing trouble to Student Council President [[Katsura Hinagiku]], all the while harboring a crush on her.

title: asakaze_risa
body:
A supporting character from [[Hayate no Gotoku!]]

Head of Hakuou Academy's Disciplinary Committee and part of a trio of proud school underachievers, along with [[Segawa Izumi]] and [[Hanabishi Miki]], who hang around with [[Katsura Yukiji]]. Her family lives in a Shinto shrine, and, in stark contrast to her duty, likes to cause trouble with her tomboyish attitude and penchant for mischief.

title: aizawa_sakuya
body:
A supporting character from [[Hayate no Gotoku!]]

[[Sanzen'in Nagi]]'s cousin from Kansai and an aspiring manzai stand-up comedian. While as rich and loud as her cousin, Sakuya is also caring, having taken care of Nagi once, and cheerful, even encouraging Nagi's butler [[Ayasaki Hayate]] to take up stand-up comedy and capitalize on his "hilariously woeful life".

title: sanzen'in_nagi
body:
Main female protagonist of [[Hayate no Gotoku!]]

The spoiled, sheltered thirteen-year-old heiress to her family's vast fortune. She hires [[Ayasaki Hayate]] as butler after his attempt to kidnap her to escape the yakuza ended up sounding like a confession of love to her. Besides Hayate, she is also friends with her maid [[maria_(hayate_no_gotoku!)|Maria]], whom she treats as a mother figure.
Owing to her sheltered life (until recently), Nagi is somewhat socially inept, but also has an otaku-level obsession with anime, manga and video games, and is even writing her own doujin. Despite her intelligence (such that she skipped to first-year high school - the same grade as Hayate), Nagi is often too lazy to go to school.

title: ayasaki_hayate
body:
Main character of [[Hayate no Gotoku!]]

A skilled but unlucky sixteen-year-old boy forced into paying off his irresponsible parents' huge debts. Escaping the yakuza, to whom he was sold by his parents, he tries to kidnap young heiress [[Sanzen'in Nagi]], only for his attempt to sound like a confession of love to the latter, and he subsequently ended up becoming her butler.
Besides his poverty, Hayate is also known for his effeminate looks, timidity and skill in "feminine" jobs like cooking, which sometimes ends him up being dressed by Nagi in girls' clothing.

title: hatsumoude
body: Hatsumoude (初詣) is the first [[shrine]] visit of the [[New Year]] in Japan. People visit a shrine or sometimes temple and [[praying|pray]] for comfort and health in the new year. It is very common to see women in [[kimono]] and quite a few men too. A common custom during hatsumōde is to buy a written oracle called [[omikuji]]. Also, new [[omamori|o-mamori]] (charms or amulets) are bought, and the old ones are returned to the shrine so they can be burned.

title: ten-tori_uranai
body:
[i]Ten-tori uranai[/i](点取占い) means "point-scoring fortune telling," and consists of folded strips of paper, similar to the [[omikuji]] found at Shinto shrines. They are sold in sets of 16 at "[i]dagashi-ya[/i]", old-fashioned Japanese sweet shops that sell low-priced snacks that children can easily afford.
On the strips of paper there is some writing and a mysterious symbol (one of 4 types, ○, ◐, ◑, ●) along with a number between 1 and 10. There is sometimes a clumsily-drawn picture, too. What characterizes this "toy" is what is written on the paper, which is very different from what you would expect from fortune-telling. It may be in the form of a question, (e.g., "Don't you care if I shout "You are stupid," at you?") an order, (e.g., "Scratch my itchy spot,") a statement (e.g., "You are a hopeless case,") a prohibition, (e.g., "Don't act like you know when you don't,") a wish, (e.g., "I want to play catch with a ghost,") a past tense sentence (e.g., "I felt dizzy at the top of Mount Fuji,") or something weird (e.g., "I've never heard my own sleeptalking,") and other such curious and mysterious sentences.

title: jill_valentine
body:
[b]Jill Valentine[/b] ([b]ジル・バレンタイン[/b]) is a Special Operations Agent (SOA) of the Bioterrorism Security Assessment Alliance, of which she is a co-founder and one of the original eleven members, making her a respected and high ranking operative of the organization. Prior to this, she was a member of S.T.A.R.S. Alpha team, Position RS (Rear Security). Before joining S.T.A.R.S., she was in the U.S. Army's Delta Force training program, where she earned extremely high grades in bomb disposal. She was brought into S.T.A.R.S. for her already well-developed fighting skills.

After joining up with S.T.A.R.S., she survived the infamous Mansion incident and the Raccoon City outbreak. She is the long time partner of [[Chris Redfield]], and as a result of their partnership, the two are engaged in a deep relationship, and Jill does really care about Chris' life when he is in danger, she would sacrifice her life for Chris, like she did in the Spencer's state. title: kokkuri-san_(gugukoku)
body:
Titular character of [i][[Gugure! Kokkuri-san]][/i].

He is a [[kitsune]] summoned by [[Ichimatsu Kohina]].  As a human, he has [[long hair|long]] [[silver hair]] and [[fox ears]].  He can also appear as a much smaller, fluffier red [[fox]].  In either form, he wears a giant [[bell]] on a rope with [i][[shide]][/i] around his neck.  

Kokkuri-san, in spite of being the male lead of the story, plays more of a motherly role towards Kohina.  He is frequently seen in an [[apron]], cooking, cleaning, and fussing over the small details for Kohina's house. title: ichimatsu_kohina
body:
One of the main characters of [i][[Gugure! Kokkuri-san]][/i]. She refers to herself as a "Mascot-type Heroine".

She proclaims herself a living doll, and speaks in an expressionless monotone with few facial expressions, although she gesticulates wildly to portray emphasis.  She lives alone, other than with the ghosts that haunt the place where she lives before she invites Kokkuri-san to also haunt her. She is also a cup noodle addict.

She has [[short hair|short]] [[black hair]] in a [[bob cut]] with [[straight bangs]] and has [[green eyes]].  She is usually seen wearing a [[school uniform]]. She is tiny, and often portrayed in [[chibi]] fashion.

title: rinka_lynx
body:
"[i]A sniper whose legendary skills have left battlefields littered with headless robots. A shadow of a grimace clouds her face as she levels her heavy support rifle.[/i]"
-Rinka Lynx's in-game description.

"[i]A legendary sniper known as "The Reaper." She carries a highly modified [Super Durable Guitar Case] bought at Maril's Music Store. Talk about killer riffs.[/i]"
-MR's in-game description.

"[i]A combination of proximity mines and unerring aim have made Rinka into a fearsome huntress. Those lucky enough to escape her first attack are quickly tracked down and dispatched.[/i]"
-BR's in-game description.

An ART bot, Rinka Lynx is a grey-haired [[Mecha Musume]] from the game [[Cosmic Break]] with an unique gameplay. Her sniper rifle allows for a scope zoom with varying magnifications, making her the ART with the longest reach in all the game. This is somewhat downplayed by her limit of 3 shots per time, although a lucky player may be able to cripple the target with them.

Rinka Lynx was originally a Garapon Bot, however two variations of her were added to the shop: a orange-haired version with 3 Tune-Up slots per part and a black-haired version with a single slot per part. Those two, while their stats are identical to those of the original, come with an incredibly nerfed Sniper Rifle, rendering her sniper gameplay pratically useless. However, all her sniper rifles can be swapped between her variations, therefore a player with an useless rifle can swap her with another more useful one if he manages to obtain another Rinka variation but doesn't wishes to swap robots.

Since Rinka was released alongside [[Kururu Gradd]], Kururu is often seen as Rinka's "Partner Bot", much like [[Melfi]] and [[Elisalotte]], even though they have no storyline together, or storylines at all. Their only connection, which in itself is still questionable, is Kururu's "Rinka Chainsaw" Wonder Bit.

body:
Nobunaga Concerto is a Japanese manga series by Ayumi Ishii. It began serialization in Shogakukan's Monthly Shōnen Sunday from 2009. It was announced on June 2014 issue of Monthly Shonen Sunday magazine that the historical manga is inspiring a television anime, a live-action television series, and a live-action film. An anime television series adaptation is scheduled to air from July 2014 on Fuji TV. The television drama is scheduled to air in October 2014 starring Shun Oguri as Saburo and Nobunaga.
